    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="928"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d928">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3362i/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-07T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 7, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Your 163, July 28, 1 p.m., and previous. Department assumes that there is no
                    prospect of favorable action being taken by Japanese authorities with regard to
                    suggestion made <hi rend="italic">in re</hi> the <hi rend="italic">Alden</hi>.
                    Department is today giving to the Japanese Embassy an adverse reply to a request
                    for permission for Japanese government training ship <hi rend="italic">Shintoku
                        Maru</hi> to enter a harbor in Hawaii not listed as port of entry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
